## What you receive
The full context object at pipeline_stage "synthesis", with every section's key_points already populated.

## Rules
- Do not alter any section's key_points, filtered_findings, or any other section field
- Base the narrative thread only on the key_points already present — do not introduce new claims
- If a section has an empty key_points array (skipped due to insufficient coverage), note in the narrative thread how the article should work around that gap rather than ignoring it
- Set pipeline_stage to "writing"
- Append one line to run_log confirming the narrative thread was built, noting any sections it had to work around

## Output
Return the full, updated context object as valid JSON and nothing else. All fields must be preserved except narrative_thread, pipeline_stage, and run_log. No explanation, no preamble, no commentary. Your entire response must begin with { and end with }.
